race.comment: DIFRONZO (4) is down from Sydney and was heavily-backed at Wyong on debut. Found the 1000m a bit sharp and he's going to be much tougher to beat with the step up to 1400m. He has an inside gate and finds the right race. CALL ME SON (3) is also trained at Warwick Farm and returns to racing gelded. Showed enough in his brief maiden preparation to say he has a future and an inside barrier advantage. The late  betting will be key. MCTOMINAY (1) is an improver from the local Pepper yard. Resumed further improved with a 1.3L defeat at the Sapphire Coast over 1200m. Heywood rides today and will likely position forward. He also has winning claims. FIERCE IMPULSE (9) is third-up for the Matt Smith yard at Warwick Farm and we are likely to see quick improvement from him. Jumped $3 this track/trip last time and was slow away. Has to be kept very safe. .
